The nasals {{IPA|/m n ɲ/}} are [[prestopped nasal consonant|prestopped]] {{IPA|[ᵇm ᵈn ᶡɲ]}} if they are preceded by an oral vowel, and [[prenasalized consonant|poststopped]] {{IPA|[mᵇ nᵈ ɲᶡ]}} if they are followed by one. The [[velar nasal]] {{IPA|/ŋ/}} is denasalized to {{IPA|[ɡ]}} before oral vowels in unstressed syllables, poststopped to {{IPA|[ŋᶢ]}} before oral vowels in stressed syllables, and prestopped {{IPA|[ᶢŋ]}} after oral vowels.

{{IPA|/h r j w/}} are [[nasalization|nasalized]] {{IPA|[h̃ r̃ w̃  ȷ̃]}} when surrounded by nasal vowels.

==Grammar==

===Pronouns===
Only [[epicene]] pronouns exist in Karitiana. This means that no distinction is made between male vs. female (as "he" or "she" in English).<ref>{{cite journal |last=Everett |first=Careb |year=2011 |title=Gender, pronouns and thought: The ligature between epicene pronouns and a more neutral gender perception |journal=Gender and Language |volume=5 |issue=1 |pages=133–152 |language=en}}</ref>

