The '''writing systems of [[Formosan languages]]''' are [[Latin alphabet|Latin]]-based alphabet systems. Currently there are 16 languages including 45 dialects are regulated. These systems consists of 48 symbols. However, some alphabets and symbols are used for different voices in different languages. The system was made official in 2005 and currently are still revising.
